HEADWORD: collectivistic
<hw>col*lec`tiv*is"tic</hw></mhw>
<pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Relating to, characteristic of, or
advocating, collectivism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>operating under collectivist principles.</def>
<note>[Narrower terms: <stype>socialistic (vs. capitalistic),
socialist</stype>; <stype>communistic</stype>]</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> collectivized, state-controlled.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>collectivise</ent>⟦br⟧
